<p>
    <img src="/Images/sripadarajaru.jpg" class="thumbnail" style="width:300px;height:300px; float:right;margin:15px;margin-top:0px" />
    Sripadaraja an eminent saint was born in Abbur near Chenna pattana to the parents Seshagiri and Giriamma.  He was given the saintly order by Sri Swarnavarna Parasurama Tirtha.  And futher he is the vidya guru of Sri Vyasaraja a great exponent of Dwaitha sidhantha.  In recognition of his great scholarship in philosophy, Sri Raghunatha Tirtha (if Uttaradi Mutt) conferred the title Sri Padaraja meaning, he is the pontiff on pontiffs.  Sri Padaraja is singularly responsible for popularizing Madhwa’s philosophy among the local population in the form of kannada songs.  Hence he is called “pitamaha” of Dasa sahitya.  All his verses and songs were written under the pen name (Ankita)  Ranga Vittala.  He also wrote a tippani (commentary on commentary) on Sriman Nyaya Sudha in the name of Vakh Vajra.  Further he write Madhwa nama which is said to be the Kannada Sri Hari Vayu Sthuthi.  He is considered to be amsa of Sri Dhruva.
</p>

<p> As a mark of his god’s grace, it is said that Ganga herself appeared on the northeast corner of Narasimha Tirtha (tank), as he was not able to go to Kasi due to old age.  His moola Brundavana is at Narasimha Tirtha (Mulubagulu in Karnataka) about 100km from Bangalore on the old Madras road.  His aradhana day falls on Jyesta Shudda Chaturdashi.
